Apple Computer is set to announce a major shift to Intel chips in its Macintosh machines, ending a long-standing partnership with IBM.
This move is seen as a response to competition from Microsoft and Sony in the home entertainment market.
Intel stands to benefit from this high-profile win, while IBM focuses on other ventures after losing Apple as a customer.
The transition to Intel chips could lead to more affordable Macs.
Apple CEO Steve Jobs expressed excitement about the switch, emphasizing Intel's strong processor roadmap.
The move is a strategic decision to ensure Apple's competitiveness in the evolving tech landscape.
